Is there a (preferably elementary) proof that the graph of the (discontinuous) function $y$ defined on $[0,1)$ by $$ y(x) =\begin{cases}
\sin\left(\dfrac{1}{x}\right) & \mbox{if $0\lt x \lt 1$,}\\\
0 & \mbox{if $x=0$,}\end{cases}$$ is not path connected?

